ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Resource consumption check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks the resource consumption from the delivered MAP file against the limits in Architektursteckbriefe

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: XML content check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if Release Notes document and supplier's AITR document (xml format)are valid XML file by the xml standards and by the XML Schema.

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: AIT version check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if AIT version stated in delivered supplier's AITR exists in the list of allowed AIT versions by Preintegration environment (Architecture).

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Release version check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if the Release label stated in delivered Release Notes exists in the lists of Acceptable Releases by Preintegration environment(Architecture).

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Check allowed compiler flags
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Reads BUILD LOG files and checks compiler and linker flags found there against the allowed ones stated in the Preintegration environment (Architecture).
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Explanation:
List of used but not allowed compiler flags: -g3, -O1, -ggdb, -D_GLIBCXX_DEBUG, -Wunused-function
List of used but not allowed linker flags: -static, -Wl,-Bdynamic, -pthread, -Wl,--dynamic-linker=/lib/ld-linux-armhf.so.3

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Compiler version check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if Compiler version stated in delivered Release Notes is accepted by the Preintegration environment (Architecture).

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: MISRA level check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Reads MISRA measurements from supplier's AITR file and checks if level is correct. If MISRA measurements not delivered within AITR file test fails.

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Is SWC buildable
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks the result of Integrator's build process.

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Memory Mapping check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks if all symbols used in component are in correct memory section.
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Comment: This test is executed for APH components only.

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Extended Version check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Compares SW-C version with the release label from the build process. Both data is given by supplier in Release Notes.
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Explanation: Check fails. Release label: SYS-D351-I3.1.1-P51.4 and SWC version: SWC-E350-I3.1.1-P51.4_20190805182946-S49.33_20190905123611

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Availability of dataset files check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: The SWC delivery is checked. If it contains the .hex files in the RN (compares RN against the delivery)

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Dataset version check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks the version found in every hex file against the version stated in RN

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Dataset filesize check
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Checks the size found in every hex file against the size projected by the Architecture Model.

ns0:TestCase.desc: Description of one Application Test Report Test Case
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Name: Check mandatory compiler/linker flags
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Description: Reads BUILD LOG files and checks compiler and linker flags found there against the mandatory ones stated in the Preintegration environment (Architecture).
ns0:TestCase.ns2:Explanation:
List of not used mandatory compiler flags: -mfpu=neon
List of not used mandatory linker flags: -lpthread
